{
  "title": "Dataset",
  "subtitle": "How the training data was formed, and exact split / family distributions from the committed JSONL files.",
  "pipeline": [
    "Synthetic scene generator (`scene.py` / `generator.py` / `olympiad_ext.py`) builds each example forward from exact coordinates, then strips those coordinates so the model input is relationships only.",
    "Labels are TikZ emission in one of two targets: v1 numeric (literal coordinates) or v2 PGF constructions (`calc` / polar / tkz-euclide) so LaTeX does the arithmetic.",
    "Every label is validated by the compile + coordinate gate (figure-only TikZ, tectonic compile, named points within \u22480.05 of ground truth). Splits are disjoint at build time.",
    "Illustrator data adds frontier distillation (`distill.py`) hard-filtered by compile + vision judge, plus broader synthetic families and paraphrases (v2 expands harder constructions)."
  ],
